cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the embedding of self-organizing inter-agent processes in distributed software applications, which is a topic related to Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) and their coordination. Therefore, cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the design and development practices for software systems, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper mentions the activation of agent modules, which could be related to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the management of (web) service infrastructures, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
